# Backend API Rules

## Route handlers

```typescript
// ✅ Validate input
const parsed = createTestSchema.safeParse(body);
if (!parsed.success) {
  return NextResponse.json({ error: { code: 'VALIDATION', message: '...' } }, { status: 400 });
}

// ✅ Typed Prisma queries
const test = await db.test.findUnique({ where: { id }, include: { steps: true } });
```

## Executor

- All HTTP execution server-side only (`src/lib/executor/`)
- Sequential steps; stop on first failure (MVP)
- Truncate stored response bodies at 256KB

## Prisma

- Use `@id @default(cuid())` for IDs
- JSON columns for step config and run snapshots
- Cascade delete: Test → Steps, TestRun → StepResults

## Errors

- Never leak stack traces to client in production
- Log server-side with context; redact secrets
